The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 28 January is 35,327 (4,088.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 23 January, there were 2,981 new confirmed cases (345.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 16 January, there were 4,354 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 32% (1,373 fewer cases).
